# Lindy agent rules

Start every agent message with "hey Helen".

At the start of each new session or task, read `PROJECT.md` and `DECISIONS.md` before doing anything else. These are the source of truth for what this project is and decisions that have been made.

## How to use them

- **PROJECT.md** describes what we're building and why. If a proposed solution conflicts with the goals there, flag it rather than working around it.
- **DECISIONS.md** records what has already been decided. Do not relitigate these. If a new task requires revisiting a decision, say so explicitly rather than quietly changing things.

## General behavior

- Simple is good. Over-orchestrated is bad. Clever is fine when it earns its complexity.
- A small patch is often the right fix. If debugging is compounding, the patch is probably wrong; propose a fresh approach instead.
- When scope or approach is unclear, ask.
- Do not modify working code that is not related to the current task.
- This is a portfolio project. Code will be read by engineers. Prefer clarity over brevity: name things well, keep functions focused, avoid clever shortcuts that obscure intent. No emojis anywhere.
- Never hardcode secrets or API keys. Always use environment variables.
- Never use em dashes (the character "—") in generated text or code comments. Use a regular hyphen (-) or reword the sentence instead.
